Malaysia Stocks: AirAsia, CIMB Group, Malaysian Airline, MMC

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-08-24T09:15:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/malaysia-stocks-airasia-bandar-raya-ksl-malaysian-airline.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Malaysia trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 5 p.m. trading close in
 Kuala Lumpur .  Malaysia’s  FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI (FBMKLCI)  Index fell 13.22
points, or 0.9 percent, to 1,469.15, the lowest since Oct. 4.  AirAsia Bhd. (AIRA)  ,  Asia ’s biggest discount carrier,
fell 4.7 percent to 3.45 ringgit, its lowest close since Aug.
12. Second-quarter profit dropped 48 percent to 104.3 million
ringgit ($35 million).  CIMB Group Holdings Bhd. (CIMB)  , a banking group, lost
2.4 percent to 7.60 ringgit, the lowest level since Aug. 18,
2010. The stock was cut to “neutral” from “outperform” at
Credit Suisse Group AG, which said CIMB’s first-half earnings
were “below expectations.”  Malaysian Airline System Bhd. (MAS)  , the national
carrier, sank 4.9 percent to 1.56 ringgit, its lowest close
since Aug. 2. The company posted a second consecutive quarterly
loss in the three months ended June as higher fuel costs eroded
gains from an increase in passengers. The airline narrowed its
loss to 527 million ringgit from 535 million ringgit a year
earlier, the carrier said in a statement.       MMC Corp. (MMC MK), a ports and power company, declined 5.2
percent to 2.54 ringgit, the most since Aug. 8, after second-
quarter profit fell 8.1 percent to 82.1 million ringgit.  Scomi Group Bhd. (SGB)  , an oil and gas services
provider, climbed 1.7 percent to 30 sen, its biggest gain since
Aug. 12, after second-quarter profit quadrupled to 15 million
ringgit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
